The German manager said: &ldquo;It&rsquo;s not that serious. He missed the departure of the plane, he missed a session and then was late for a meal &hellip; I have to build a group here, I have to start anew, so I thought it maybe made sense that he flew home to Liverpool and after eight days, when we come back, we can talk about it.<br />
<br />
&ldquo;But it&rsquo;s not that serious. It is how I said, we have some rules and we have to respect them. If somebody doesn&rsquo;t respect it, or somebody gives me the feeling he is not respecting it, then I have to react, that&rsquo;s all.&rdquo;

Suarez: &quot;Liverpool look like they are in a good position to qualify for the Champions League - hopefully they'll be back where they belong.&quot;<br />
<br />
Suarez: &quot;Liverpool will always be a special club to me - and I know what playing in the Champions League means to the players and fans.&quot;

Andros Townsend: &quot;Obviously I am not the chairman but you have seen the impact #Sakho has had since he&rsquo;s come in. He's been incredible.&quot;<br />
<br />
Townsend: &quot;#Sakho is an incredible player and we should do all we can, if we survive, to keep him here next season.&quot;
